<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Card with Transition Effect</title>
  <style>
    /* Basic reset */
* {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    
  }
  
  body {
    font-family:Arial,  sans-serif;
    background-color:chartreuse;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    height: 100vh;
  }
  
  /* Card Container */
  .card-container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 20px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding: 20px;
  }
  
  /* Card Styles */
  .card {
    background-color: white;
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    width: 300px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease, background-color 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .card img {
    width:auto;
    height:auto;
    object-fit:fill;
  }
  
  .card h3 {
    padding: 10px;
    font-size: 1.5em;
    color: #333;
  }
  
  .card p {
    padding: 0 10px 10px;
    color: #666;
  }
  
  .card button {
    padding: 10px;
    width: 100%;
    border: none;
    background-color:blue;
    color: white;
    font-size: 1em;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .card button:hover {
    background-color: #ff5733;
  }
  
  /* Hover Effect */
  .card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-10px); /* Lift the card on hover */
    box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2); /* Deeper shadow */
    background-color: #fafafa; /* Slight background color change */
  }
  center,font ,  strong{
    
    padding-top: 20px;
  }
    button{
        margin-left: 0px;
        margin-top: 0px;
        text-align: center;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        background-color:goldenrod;
    }

  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="card-container">
    <div class="card">
      <img src="easy1.jpeg" style="height:500px; width:300px;" alt="Card Image">
      <h3>LEVEL-1 Easy</h3>
      <p>It is the level1 of the CSS quiz with the help of which you can start fron easy and to proceed towards advance.</p>
      <button onclick="window.location.href='css-quiz.html'">START</button>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <img src="medium.jpeg" style="height: 450px; width:300px;" alt="Card Image">
      <h3>LEVEL-2 Medium</h3>
      <P>Now you reach level2 of CSS  and you have basic knowledge so move towards hard.</p>
      <button onclick="window.location.href='css-level2.html'">START</button>
      <center><font size="10px" color="red"><strong>G</strong>ood</font></center>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <img src="hard1.png" style="height: 400px; width:300px;" alt="Card Image">
      <h3>Level-3 Hard</h3>
      <p>Congratulates you are at the hard level of CSS with you can bost your memory.</p>
      <button onclick="window.location.href='css-level3.html'">START</button>
      <center><font size="10px" color="red"><strong>E</strong>xcellent</font></center>
    </div>
  </div>
  <button onclick="window.location.href='dashboard.html'"><font size="40px" color="red">Back</font></button>
</body>
</html>
